<div id="banner">
	<h1>The Search for Sight</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Wired Magazine: <a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/10.09/vision_pr.html">Vision Quest</a>. The riveting story of a blind man and the scientists who&#8217;ve used cameras, computers and neural stimulators to get him to see.</p><blockquote>&#8220;The next version,&#8221; Dobelle tells me, &#8220;may have enough resolution to use while driving in traffic.&#8221; In fact, since this is only a simple camera we&#8217;re talking about, one could imagine the addition of any number of superhuman optical features: night vision, X-ray vision, microscopic focus, long-range zoom. Forget the camera even; there&#8217;s no reason you couldn&#8217;t jack directly into the Net. In the future, the disabled may prove <em>more</em> abled; we may all want their prostheses.</blockquote><p>Exciting times.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 14, 2002 09:20 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000509" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
